Paper: hep-th/9604115

Date: 1996-04-19

Title: Non-commutative Geometry Beyond the Standard Model

Authors: Igor Pris, Thomas Schucker (Marseille)

Comments: 12 pages, LaTeX, one error eliminated, published version

Journal-ref: J.Math.Phys. 38 (1997) 2255-2265

A natural extension of the standard model within non-commutative geometry ispresented. The geometry determines its Higgs sector. This determination isfuzzy, but precise enough to be incompatible with experiment.